CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 28, 1941, page 8, reads: "These popular Philadelphians said 'hello' to Pittsburgh Monday when they stopped enroute to Chicago. They are Doris Christmas, Mr. McNeil, their cousin, Mrs. Alice Christmas, Doris' mother. The trip is really Doris' having graduated from Virginia State College this month and wanting to see the big bad world a bit before settling down to be somebody's secretary. They visited with the Henr... Lindsays. Charles Catlins and Ira Lewises. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Doris Christmas, Harriet Lewis, and Alice Christmas, seated behind Mr. McNeil, on bench in garden of Ira Lewis residence, 616 Wilkinsburg Avenue, Homewood
